Possibly the best thing about an offline music library is that the software I use to manage it supports "AutoPlaylists" that effectively run a query against your library database and build the playlist dynamically to your specifications.

Bair can actually combo into falling upair/aNair1 at really early percents, it's just normally not possible because it can't reverse hit (bad gaem or something) so you can't usually face the opponent after hitting it. 

dk is terrible though https://t.co/a8ntzAtC7Q

They also have a 5-star rating system that supports 1/2 stars, so if you're willing to spend the time tagging and rating your files it becomes incredibly powerful. Like I now have fully auto >=4â˜… playlists for my entire library, only instrumentals, and non-instrumental tracks.

It's kind of crazy to me that streaming platforms will build you playlists based on their algorithm, but generally won't let you define your own dynamic playlists based on the tracks you've saved to your library
